CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 6, 1960, pg. A9 reads: "With The Fredericks - Mr. and Mrs. William Frederick, at whose home the Frogs entertained their wives and out-of-town guests at a breakfast following the formal on Friday night, are pictured with some of their guests. Left to right: Mr. and Mrs. Alvin Harrell, Harrisburg; Mrs. Max Johnson and Dr. Johnson, Aliquippa; the Fredericks; Mrs. Charles Busby and Mr. Busby, Wheeling, W.Va., and Mrs. Walter Cole and Mr. Cole of Harrisburg. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Mr. and Mrs. Alvin Harrell, Dr. and Mrs. Max Johnson, William Frederick, LaRue Frederick, Mr. and Mrs.Charles Busby, and Mr. and Mrs. Walter Cole, posed in front of wooden fence, in yard of Mr. and Mrs. William Frederick for breakfast party after FROGS formal, Oakmont
